Commentary Text: Bumrah to Kohli, out Caught by Saurabh Tiwary! There was a lot of pressure on Tiwary to take this one, and a lot of time to think about the pressure with the ball in the air. Kohli happens to be Bumrah's 100th IPL wicket - how fitting is that? Bangs a short one into the wicket at 143km/h, Kohli fetches the pull from outside off and gets a bit top-edge that flies high in the air, and Tiwari at short midwicket, who isn't the fittest, is moving without a lot of balance and manages to hold onto it - and his knees give way as he topples over without spilling it. Kohli c Saurabh Tiwary b Bumrah 9(14)

Commentary Text: Rahul Chahar to Philippe, out Stumped!! The use of the feet, in fact, has cost him. Though he hasn't really raced forward, Philippe wanted to tonk another biggie and swung hard at this loopy legbreak from Rahul Chahar. Got beaten by the drift and QDK's quick relflexes ensure Philippe's short. Dragged his back foot too far and by the time the bails came off, the foot was still in the air. Easy call for the telly umpire. Philippe st de Kock b Rahul Chahar 33(24) [4s-4 6s-1]

Commentary Text: Chahal to Krunal Pandya, out Caught by Chris Morris!! Brainless cricket from Krunal Pandya. That was tossed up wider, Krunal Pandya had to reach out a bit and ended up slicing it to the man at long-off. Poor cricket as it had already turned out to be a fruitful over. Krunal Pandya I guess got overawed from the other end. Not something MI needed now. Very well thought out by Chahal as he lured Pandya with a wider one. Commentary Text: Chahal to Ishan Kishan, out Caught by Chris Morris !! Lovely lovely bowling from Chahal - threw this leg-break invitingly outside off, Kishan came charging down the pitch, didn't get anywhere close to the ball, he still went ahead with the lofted drive, came right off the toe-end, high and towards long-off. Morris has plenty of time to settle under it, he watches it closely and holds on. Big wicket for RCB - Kishan had made 99 when they last played him. Jayawardene looks pensive in the MI dug-out. Ishan Kishan c Chris Morris b Chahal 25(19) [4s-3 6s-1]
